<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>Changing Color of HTML Text Using JavaScript</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>JavaScript can change the color of HTML text.</p>
    <p>Watch the color change!</p>
    
    <button onclick="changeColor()">Click here!</button>

    <p id="change">Good Morning!</p>

    <script>
      function changeColor() {
        document.getElementById("change").style.color = "aqua";
      }
    </script>
  </body>
